教育・子ども・地域をつなぐ活動に取り組む。
東日本大震災を機に、教育現場の変化のなさに疑問を抱き、子ども中心の学びを模索。
保護者としての実体験を通して、進路支援・環境整備・自治体連携など、さまざまな支援活動を展開中。
現在は協働と対話をキーワードに、誰もが自分らしく学べる社会の実現を目指す。

 English:

Connecting education, children, and communities.
After returning to Fukuoka post-3.11, I questioned the stagnation of school environments and began advocating for student-centered learning.
Based on real-life parenting experiences, I support families with educational guidance, institutional collaboration, and community outreach.
Currently exploring co-creation and dialogue to build inclusive learning spaces.